<h1>Editorial Policy</h1>

<p>
At everydaymoneylab, our mission is to publish practical, accurate, and trustworthy financial information that helps readers make better money decisions.
</p>

<h2>Our Editorial Principles</h2>

<ul>
<li>Accuracy comes before speed.</li>
<li>Content is written for readers, not search engines.</li>
<li>Recommendations are based on research and evidence.</li>
<li>Editorial decisions are independent of advertisers and affiliate partners.</li>
<li>When information changes, we update our content whenever possible.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Research Process</h2>

<p>
Our articles are created using information from government agencies, financial institutions, academic research, industry reports, and other reputable public sources. We compare multiple sources before publishing information whenever practical.
</p>

<h2>Editorial Independence</h2>

<p>
Advertising, sponsorships, or affiliate relationships do not influence our editorial opinions. Any commercial relationships are disclosed separately where required.
</p>

<h2>Corrections</h2>

<p>
Despite careful research, mistakes can happen. If an error is identified, we review it and make corrections as quickly as possible.
</p>

<h2>Content Updates</h2>

<p>
Financial information changes over time. We periodically review important articles and update them to improve accuracy and relevance.
</p>

<h2>Our Commitment</h2>

<p>
Our goal is to build a publication that readers can trust for clear, practical, and unbiased financial education—without hype, unnecessary complexity, or misleading claims.
</p>

</article>
